# Booking Handoff: {{persona_first_name}}

> [!warning] AUTO-SEND TEMPLATE
> When a prospect replies with interest, the agent sends this body verbatim with NO human review. Read every word. Fix what's wrong before your first deploy.

## When to use

When ALL of these hold:
- Prospect classified as "interested"
- Confidence score >= {{preferences.confidence_floor}}
- Daily auto-send cap not hit
- Booking URL present for {{persona_first_name}}

## Variables

The drafter substitutes these at send time:

- `{first_name}` — prospect's first name
- `{company}` — prospect's company
- `{booking_url}` — calendar link from booking-links.md
- `{sender_signature}` — {{persona_first_name}}'s email signature

## Body (verbatim — sent as-is)

```
Hey {first_name},

Glad it caught you. Easiest is grabbing a slot here: {booking_url}

15 mins, no pitch. I'll show you what's relevant to {company} and you can decide from there.

{sender_signature}
```

## Quality checklist (verify before first deploy)

- [ ] Reads naturally with a real first_name + company name
- [ ] No banned brand-voice words
- [ ] No em dashes (regular hyphens / periods only)
- [ ] No price numbers or claims
- [ ] One clear CTA (booking link)
- [ ] Tone matches {{persona_first_name}}'s voice
- [ ] Signature is accurate

## What to do if this template feels off

Edit the body block above. Save. The auto-send path unlocks once you save. Until then, all replies to {{persona_first_name}} fall back to review-first (you approve in Telegram).

